ANTHRAX - ARGENTINA (11): (BUENOS AIRES) BOVINE
***********************************************
A ProMED-mail post
http://www.promedmail.org
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
http://www.isid.org

Date: Tue 19 Nov 2013
From: Ramon Noseda <rnoseda@laboratorioazul.com.ar> [edited]


Outbreak of anthrax in Daireaux, Province of Buenos Aires
---------------------------------------------------------
_Bacillus anthracis_ has been isolated from an adult cow, one of 6 that died suddenly in the past week [11-15 Nov 2013], in a herd of 600 head. All the deaths were acute and with extravasation of blood from their natural openings [nose, vagina, anus, etc] The owner expecting this diagnosis has initiated vaccination.

Although advised by his veterinarian this herd had not been previously vaccinated. The estancia is in the partido [a 2nd level administrative division] of Daireaux in the paraje [county] of La Nevada in the west of the province of Buenos Aires. Latterly there have been heavy rains which have soaked the pastures. The last known outbreak that was registered for this partido in the rural surveillance programme was in 2005. No ranch hands were at risk handling this carcass.

It should be noted that the unitary cost of a Sterne vaccination is ARS [pesos] 1.20, while the replacement cost of a cow is ARS 3800 [or 20 US cents vs USD 634.45 at ARS 5.98 per USD, ref Economist 16 Nov 2013. - Mod.MHJ]

